                xml:id="ttag32"
                ref="#person_445"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag32" type="person">
          Pythagoras
        </name>
            </rs> and<lb/>
his Early followers but many of them and<lb/>
particularly <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag33"
                ref="#person_1043"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag33" type="person">
          Ocellus
        </name>
            </rs> considered matter as having<lb/>
constantly existed in form similar to its<lb/>
present arrangement.<lb/>
And <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Timaus</del>
