                rend="underline">the Sun</hi> which he supposed<lb/>
to revolve round the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">moon</hi>.<lb/>
He considered the Earth as flat and<lb/>
the sea as constantly diminishing and<lb/>
He vainly predicted that at some time<lb/>
the whole surface would be dry land -<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="26"
                xml:id="pb-26"
                facs="#i26"/>
            <lb/>
The only immediate follower of any<lb/>
reputation was likewise of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag51"
                ref="#place_1133"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag51" type="place">
          Abdera
        </name>
            </rs> He<lb/>
lived about 400 years before <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag52"
                ref="#person_951"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag52" type="person">
          Christ
        </name>
            </rs> and<lb/>
was reputed to be an observer and an<lb/>
