labour -<lb/>
From the time of Anagorus: Words<lb/>
had been multiplying; though few new<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="28"
                xml:id="pb-28"
                facs="#i28"/>
            <lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">observations</hi> had been made.<lb/>
And whilst theories of Cosmogony were<lb/>
almost infinitely varied no accurate<lb/>
knowledge concerning the materials<lb/>
of the Globe had been obtained -<lb/>
Almost every studient that He could<lb/>
explain what the Globe was in remote<lb/>
antiquity and what it would be in<lb/>
future ages: but no one examined<lb/>
its present state and the nature of<lb/>
its different parts -<lb/>
Every disciple of the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag53"
                ref="#person_445"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag53" type="person">
          Pythagorean
        </name>
            </rs>
            <lb/>
School confidently believed that He knew<lb/>
